  <info>
    <title>Creating logical block volumes</title>
    <meta name="maintainer" content="jsindelarova@suse.com" its:translate="no"/>
    <abstract>
      <para>
        The following topic describes how to create a block volume from an
        existing volume group.
      </para>
    </abstract>
  </info>
  <para>
    If you have a volume group, you can create a logical block volume from it.
    To do so, proceed as follows:
  </para>
  <procedure>
    <step>
      <para>
        Navigate to the <guimenu>Storage</guimenu> page.
      </para>
    </step>
    <step>
      <para>
        In the <guimenu>Devices</guimenu>, click the volume group you want to
        use.
      </para>
    </step>
    <step>
      <para>
        Click <guimenu>Create new logical volume</guimenu>
      </para>
    </step>
    <step>
      <para>
        Specify a logical volume name. select a block device and select the
        size to use.
      </para>
    </step>
    <step>
      <para>
        Select the <guimenu>Block device for filesystems</guimenu>.
      </para>
    </step>
    <step>
      <para>
        Select the size to use.
      </para>
    </step>
    <step>
      <para>
        Click <guimenu>Create</guimenu> to confirm the details.
      </para>
    </step>
    <step>
      <para>
        Format the block volume by clicking <guimenu>Format</guimenu> and
        filling the details as described in
        <xref linkend="formatting-filesystems-details" xrefstyle="template:formatting file systems"/>.
      </para>
    </step>
  </procedure>
</topic>
